WEBVTT

00:06.174 --> 00:09.910
[ Chattering ]

00:16.384 --> 00:19.387
- WE'RE HERE TO LOOK
AT THE EXECUTIVE WASHROOM.
- WHAT DO YOU NEED?

00:19.420 --> 00:21.889
I LEFT MY CELL PHONE ON 17.
LADY, I CAN'T BE
ANY CLEARER.

00:21.922 --> 00:25.893
- MY PURSE IS IN MY OFFICE.
- NO ELEVATOR SERVICE
ABOVE THE 15th FLOOR.

00:25.926 --> 00:29.063
- CLEARANCE FOR SNAKE DOCTOR
AND ASSOCIATES?
- NO ONE GOES UP THE ELEVATOR.

00:29.097 --> 00:32.666
SO MAKE YOURSELF COMFORTABLE.

00:32.700 --> 00:36.404
CALL UPSTAIRS. ASK YOUR BOSS,
SPECIAL AGENT BLUMAN.
TELL HIM SNAKE DOCTOR'S HERE.

00:36.437 --> 00:38.472
YOU HAVE ANY I.D.?

00:49.983 --> 00:53.487
EVERYBODY ELSE, STAY BACK.
[ Woman ]
WHY DO THEY GET TO GO UP?

00:55.789 --> 00:58.092
STAY BACK. STAY BACK.

01:40.334 --> 01:42.936
- AGENT BLUMAN.
- MR. BLUE.
MR. GREEN AND MR. WHITE.

01:42.970 --> 01:46.940
THAT'S BANK C.E.O. VAN WALCOTT.
COMES IN THIS MORNING FOR
THE WEEKLY EXECUTIVE MEETING.

01:46.974 --> 01:49.377
TAPED TO THE DOOR WAS THIS.

01:52.146 --> 01:54.215
THEN HE OPENS THE DOOR,
FINDS THAT.

01:58.319 --> 02:01.489
BOMB DISARMAMENT 101.
YOU FREEZE THE PARTS,
STOP THE DETONATOR.

02:01.522 --> 02:04.292
WE'RE AWARE OF THE TECHNIQUE.
ANY IDEA WHAT
THE SECOND NOTE SAYS?

02:04.325 --> 02:06.794
ALREADY DOESN'T WANT US
TO LET ANYONE OUT
OR HE'LL SET IT OFF.

02:06.827 --> 02:09.697
MY GUESS IS IT'S
UPHILL FROM THERE.
WHAT DO YOU THINK?

02:09.730 --> 02:12.500
I THINK THIS IS A BANK,
WHICH MAKES IT FEDERAL,
WHICH PUTS YOU IN CHARGE.

02:12.533 --> 02:14.868
AND I THINK I SHOULD BE
ON VACATION.

02:14.902 --> 02:18.772
BUT IF YOU WEREN'T,
AND YOU WERE BROUGHT HERE
TO OBSERVE AND ADVISE?

02:18.806 --> 02:20.608
NEED TO SEE THE OTHER NOTE.

02:20.641 --> 02:23.977
- THEN HOW MANY FOLKS
IN THE BUILDING?
- 650.

02:24.011 --> 02:27.147
WE GOTTA HOSE 'EM
ALL OUTTA HERE.

02:36.657 --> 02:40.661
[ Grey ]
SMELLS LIKE 1980, LAKE TAHOE,
HARVEY CASINO'S RENOVATION.

02:40.694 --> 02:44.498
GOD HELP US IF YOU'RE RIGHT.
BUT WE'RE HERE TO
ADVISE AND ASSIST.

02:44.532 --> 02:48.469
WE'RE NOT CALLING
THIS ONE.
DON'T LET 'EM FREEZE IT.

02:48.502 --> 02:51.171
TELL ME.
I BUILT SOMETHING
THAT GOOD-LOOKING,

02:51.205 --> 02:55.643
FIRST THING I'D EXPECT
IS THE BOMB SQUAD WOULD TRY
AND TURN IT INTO AN ICE CUBE.

02:55.676 --> 02:58.712
WHAT'S THE CALL?
FIND OUT IF THERE'S
REALLY A TIMER.

02:58.746 --> 03:01.215
THEN HOW MUCH JUICE
IT'S GOT.

03:01.249 --> 03:03.384
WHO ARE THESE MEN?
PROS FROM DOVER.

03:03.417 --> 03:05.419
STOP THE FREEZE.
WHAT?

03:05.453 --> 03:09.557
MR. WHITE THINKS THERE MIGHT
BE A MERCURY SWITCH. COOL
IT DOWN, MERCURY SETS IT OFF.

03:09.590 --> 03:11.725
WE CHECKED THE X-RAYS.
[ Walcott ]
WHAT ABOUT THE BLIND SPOTS?

03:11.759 --> 03:14.562
- WHAT BLIND SPOTS?
- YOU'RE PUNTING ON FIRST DOWN.

03:14.595 --> 03:17.164
- SHOW ME.
- CAN YOU GET A LITTLE TIGHTER
WITH THE TALON?

03:17.197 --> 03:19.767
I'VE GOT TWO VISUALS,
BUT STATIONARY.
HE'S GOT MOBILITY.

03:19.800 --> 03:22.536
CAN I SEE THE REST
OF THOSE?
DO WE WANT THESE GUYS HERE?

03:22.570 --> 03:27.174
IF THIS GOES BAD, NOBODY KNOWS
WHO THEY ARE AND THEY GOT NO
PAPER TRAIL. ANY MORE QUESTIONS?

03:27.207 --> 03:30.010
- I GOTTA TAKE A LEAK.
- NOT THAT WAY.

03:30.043 --> 03:32.546
THERE.

03:47.761 --> 03:51.064
NO WAY. DUDE'S NOT EVEN
WEARING A BOMB SUIT.

03:51.098 --> 03:55.969
IF THIS IS THE REAL DEAL
AND THE BOMB GOES, SUIT
WOULDN'T DO HIM ANY GOOD.

03:56.003 --> 03:58.839
IN WHICH CASE, I GOT BAD NEWS
FOR THE REST OF US.

04:26.266 --> 04:29.136
SOMEONE LOOKING
FOR FIVE MILLION?

04:29.169 --> 04:31.339
AT LEAST WE KNOW
IT'S NOT TERRORISTS.

04:31.372 --> 04:35.409
HOW'S THAT?
WE WOULDN'T BE HAVING
A CONVERSATION IN THE BUILDING.

04:35.443 --> 04:38.312
IT'D BE GONE ALREADY.

04:38.346 --> 04:40.981
[ Man ]
WHAT'S HE DOING NOW?

04:46.720 --> 04:49.790
HE'S GONE
TO A BLIND SPOT.

04:49.823 --> 04:52.793
WHAT DOES HE WANT?

04:52.826 --> 04:56.296
HE'S LOOKING FOR THE MERCURY
SWITCH. LITTLE FELLA
THAT LOOKS LIKE THIS.

04:58.632 --> 05:02.536
FREEZE THE BOMB, THE MERCURY
WILL MAKE IT GO POP.

05:02.570 --> 05:05.339
PULL IN, SEE IF YOU CAN'T
ZOOM IN ON HIS HAND.

05:11.244 --> 05:13.514
WHAT-- WHAT'S HE DOING?

05:13.547 --> 05:15.315
SHOWING US THE MERCURY.

05:17.551 --> 05:20.087
STOP THE FREEZE.

05:21.154 --> 05:23.824
NO NEED.

05:23.857 --> 05:27.127
- YOUR GUY ALREADY DID IT.
- [ Sighs ]

05:27.160 --> 05:31.331
LOOK. I KNOW WE'RE MERELY
HERE AS ADVISERS,

05:31.365 --> 05:35.168
BUT CAN WE ALL AGREE THAT
THE GOAL IS NOT TO BLOW UP
EVERYONE IN THE BUILDING?

05:39.740 --> 05:42.209
[ Call And Response ]
* FIRED UP
FIRED UP *

05:42.242 --> 05:44.344
* TWENTY-SEVEN
FIRED UP *

05:44.378 --> 05:46.814
* HERE WE GO
ON THE ROAD *

05:46.847 --> 05:49.182
* TWENTY-SEVEN
FIRED UP *

05:49.216 --> 05:51.318
* FIRED UP
FIRED UP *

05:51.351 --> 05:54.221
* TWENTY-SEVEN
FIRED UP *

06:04.097 --> 06:07.367
YOU REALIZE HOW MANY
REGULATIONS OF SAFETY
YOUR MAN JUST VIOLATED?

06:07.401 --> 06:10.237
- HOW MANY?
- NEVER MIND SUPERSEDING
MY AUTHORITY.

06:10.270 --> 06:14.141
NO, I WON'T MIND BECAUSE AT
THE MOMENT, YOU HAVE BIGGER FISH
TO FRY-- 650 OF THEM.

06:16.544 --> 06:19.613
- TALK TO ME.
- WE GOTTA GET BUSY.
IT COULD BE A KIT CAR.

06:19.647 --> 06:21.849
ON THE OUTSIDE,
IT LOOKS LIKE A FERRARI.

06:21.882 --> 06:24.618
LAKE TAHOE WAS THE OPPOSITE.
GREMLIN ON THE OUTSIDE,
FERRARI INSIDE.

06:24.652 --> 06:28.121
LAKE TAHOE?
BOOM.

06:32.893 --> 06:36.930
[ Grey ] ALL RIGHT.
YOUR MAN IS TALKING
TO HIMSELF.

06:36.964 --> 06:40.934
STANDARD O.P.
WE HAVE TO SEND
OUR EVERY MOVE BACK HOME.

06:40.968 --> 06:44.605
THINGS GO POP,
SOMEONE KNOWS WHY.

06:52.179 --> 06:55.315
WHAT WAS WRONG
WITH THE OLD ROOM?
THE OLD ROOM HAD AN OCEAN VIEW.

06:55.348 --> 06:58.151
IT WAS A SMOKING ROOM.
AND I SPECIFICALLY ASKED
FOR A NONSMOKING ROOM.

06:58.185 --> 07:01.121
IT SMELLED LIKE
CIGARETTE SMOKE.
CIGARETTE SMOKE?

07:01.154 --> 07:04.424
IT SMELLED STALE.
COULD YOU HAVE
AT LEAST TOLD ME?

07:04.458 --> 07:09.463
WELL, YOU WERE OUT SHOPPING.

07:09.497 --> 07:13.000
IS IT IMPORTANT?
NO, YOU'RE RIGHT.

07:13.033 --> 07:16.570
THANK YOU.
THE HARD PART'S CHANGING GEARS.

07:16.604 --> 07:19.006
"CHANGING GEARS."
IT'S THE WHOLE THING, BABY.

07:19.039 --> 07:21.141
GEARING DOWN AND DECOMPRESSING.

07:21.174 --> 07:24.578
AND I GOTTA GET OUTTA MY MAMA
BAG AND LET'S BE ON VACATION.

07:24.612 --> 07:26.747
AND I'M SORRY.
AND I BEG YOUR PARDON.

07:26.780 --> 07:29.683
FOR WHAT?
FOR CARPING AT YOU LIKE YOU
FORGOT TO CLEAR THE TABLE.

07:29.717 --> 07:34.522
AH.
AND I'LL FIX UP
THE NEW ROOM.

07:38.526 --> 07:41.595
[ Man ]
YOU MUST BE THE NEW NEIGHBORS.
THIS HERE'S MY HUSBAND BOB.

07:41.629 --> 07:44.865
- AND HE'S GOT AN 11 HANDICAP.
- REALLY? AN 11?

07:44.898 --> 07:48.268
WHERE DO YOU PLAY, BOB?
EVERY COURSE AROUND
FORT GRIFFITH.

07:48.301 --> 07:51.004
YOU DOWN HERE
ON A MILITARY DISCOUNT?
YEAH. YOU TOO?

07:51.038 --> 07:54.608
- JOEL BOWMAN.
AIR FORCE RESEARCH, KIRTLAND.
- BOB BROWN, ARMY, LOGISTICS.

07:54.642 --> 07:56.777
I HATE TO THINK WHAT CIVILIANS
PAY FOR THIS PLACE.

07:56.810 --> 07:58.779
[ Laughing ]
BRING YOUR CLUBS?

07:58.812 --> 08:02.650
WELL, MY WIFE AND I
WERE, UM--

08:02.683 --> 08:06.153
WELL, I WOULDN'T
WANT TO IMPOSE.
YOU BRING YOUR CLUBS?

08:08.221 --> 08:10.157
WELL, YEAH, I DID.

08:10.190 --> 08:13.561
- HI.
- HI.

08:19.399 --> 08:22.169
[ Clears Throat ]

08:26.206 --> 08:28.909
NOTE SAYS IT'S SET
TO GO OFF IN 24 HOURS.

08:28.942 --> 08:31.378
BE NICE TO KNOW 24 HOURS
FROM WHEN, WOULDN'T IT?

08:31.411 --> 08:34.682
- MR. WHITE, YOU WANT
TO WORK YOUR MAGIC?
- IT'S MESSING WITH US.

08:34.715 --> 08:38.151
ALL THESE BLIND SPOTS.
SOME REALLY HIDING SOMETHING,
OTHERS JUST A BLIND ALLEY.

08:38.185 --> 08:41.722
- LIKE HIDE-AND-SEEK.
- WHY DON'T YOU READ ME SOME
MORE OF THOSE BLIND SPOTS?

08:41.755 --> 08:44.491
TELL ME WHAT YOU SEE.
COPY. LET ME KNOW
WHEN YOU'RE READY.

08:44.524 --> 08:47.260
GENTLEMEN, WE'RE GOING IN.

09:24.431 --> 09:27.100
OKAY, BOSS.
READY TO GO.

09:27.134 --> 09:31.839
ALL RIGHT, HERE GOES.
BOTTOM MIDDLE BY SIX INCHES.

09:34.474 --> 09:38.946
TOP BOX UNDERNEATH
THE SEVENTH SWITCH.

09:38.979 --> 09:43.684
LOWER MOTOR, ALL AROUND
TABLETOP TO 10 INCHES.

10:06.539 --> 10:09.777
YOU PUSH THE GAS,
I'LL STEER.

10:20.854 --> 10:23.791
ONE.

10:24.992 --> 10:26.660
- TWO.
- WAIT.

10:26.694 --> 10:29.329
GO BACK.
LESS THAN ONE.

10:31.865 --> 10:34.501
- GOT A WHIRLING SOUND,
LIKE A HUMMINGBIRD.
- TIMER?

10:34.534 --> 10:38.305
- AFFIRMATIVE.
- IT'S ARMED AND DANGEROUS.

10:38.338 --> 10:40.540
DON'T KNOW WHEN BUT
THIS THING'S PRIMED TO BLOW.

10:40.573 --> 10:45.612
MR. GREEN,
YOU GUYS STAY ON THE TIMER.
MAKE IT STOP.

10:45.645 --> 10:47.647
MR. WHITE,
HOW MUCH HORSEPOWER?

10:47.681 --> 10:50.718
- YOU LOOKING AT THE X-RAY?
- I AM NOW.

10:50.751 --> 10:54.688
CAN YOU SEE THIS
FROM HERE TO HERE?

10:54.722 --> 10:57.390
AFFIRMATIVE.

10:57.424 --> 11:00.894
- I'M THINKING 35
TO 45 POUND C-4.
- COPY.

11:12.572 --> 11:14.507
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

11:14.541 --> 11:17.077
GONNA GET PERSONAL WITH IT.

11:19.880 --> 11:23.383
CAREFUL. SHE BITES.

11:23.416 --> 11:26.754
YOU'RE LUCKY
YOU GOT HERE ONLY YESTERDAY.

11:26.787 --> 11:30.257
IT WAS RAINING THE TWO DAYS
BEFORE THAT.

11:30.290 --> 11:33.260
IT MUST BE NICE TRAVELING
WITH A BUILT-IN BABYSITTER.

11:33.293 --> 11:35.428
EVELYN'S WONDERFUL.

11:35.462 --> 11:39.099
WE GOT MY MOM TO WATCH
OUR SERENA. THEY'RE BACK
AT HER PLACE IN TEXAS.

11:39.132 --> 11:42.736
SO THIS IS THE LAST
LITTLE GETAWAY BEFORE,
HUH? NICE.

11:42.770 --> 11:45.605
SO I ASSUME
YOU'RE NOT A SMOKER.
NO.

11:45.638 --> 11:49.843
GOOD. THE PEOPLE
BEFORE YOU IN THAT ROOM,
THEY SMOKED LIKE CHIMNEYS.

11:49.877 --> 11:53.713
- WE COULD SMELL IT
THROUGH THE WALLS.
- YOU MEAN IN OUR ROOM?

11:55.615 --> 11:59.619
- I DIDN'T SMELL ANYTHING.
- HOTEL MUST'VE AIRED IT OUT.

11:59.652 --> 12:04.424
ANYWAYS, I'M GLAD THEY'RE GONE.
THEY WEREN'T FRIENDLY
LIKE YOU EITHER.

12:04.457 --> 12:06.526
[ Bob ]
WHERE DO YOU PLAY IN L.A.?

12:06.559 --> 12:10.363
BELIEVE IT OR NOT,
I ACTUALLY USED TO WORK
AT THE RIVIERA.

12:10.397 --> 12:12.465
- DID YOU REALLY?
- LOOK AT THAT.

12:12.499 --> 12:14.567
FOR LIKE A SUMMER.
HOW DID YOU DO, HONEY?

12:14.601 --> 12:18.138
THIS GUY, YOU SHOULD SEE
HIS SWING. YOU SURE
YOU DON'T WANT ONE?

12:18.171 --> 12:21.641
- I THOUGHT THAT WAS
A VICTORY CIGAR.
- YOU LET ME WIN.

12:21.674 --> 12:25.278
WHAT I WAS DOING IS CALLED
LOSING. WE'RE GONNA GO
GET A SANDWICH, OKAY?

12:25.312 --> 12:29.049
- WHEN?
- WELL, RIGHT NOW. WHAT?

12:29.082 --> 12:33.486
- WE'RE SUPPOSED TO CALL
SERENA IN 15 MINUTES?
- AH! WOULD YOU DO IT?

12:33.520 --> 12:37.157
OKAY, THANKS.
LET'S GO.

12:38.826 --> 12:41.661
HI, BABY BOO-BOO.
SAY HELLO TO DADDY.

12:41.694 --> 12:44.965
WELL, THEY DON'T ALWAYS LEAVE
WITH THE ONES THEY CAME IN WITH.

12:49.469 --> 12:53.273
EXCUSE ME. MRS. BROWN?
I HOPE YOU'RE ENJOYING
YOUR STAY.

12:53.306 --> 12:56.309
THANKS, YES.
YOU'VE GOT A VERY ROMANTIC
HUSBAND, MRS. BROWN.

12:56.343 --> 12:58.912
I DO?
HE'S WILLING TO PAY A LOT...

12:58.946 --> 13:01.148
TO GET HIS WIFE
THE SAME SUITE YOU HAD
ON YOUR HONEYMOON.

13:01.181 --> 13:03.516
EXCUSE ME?
I'M JUST SAYING
A LOT OF HUSBANDS...

13:03.550 --> 13:05.485
I SEE HERE AREN'T
SO CONSIDERATE.

13:05.518 --> 13:07.487
HAVE A GOOD DAY.

13:15.328 --> 13:19.132
[ Beeping ]

13:19.166 --> 13:23.136
[ Beeping ]

13:24.704 --> 13:27.374
- OH, HEY, BABE.
- I CALLED SERENA.

13:27.407 --> 13:29.576
YEAH? GOOD.
IT WAS BEEPING.

13:31.078 --> 13:32.712
THANK YOU.

13:32.745 --> 13:35.448
- AMY SEEMS NICE.
- YEAH, SHE DOES.

13:35.482 --> 13:38.185
SHE WANTS TO KNOW
IF THE FOUR OF US CAN ALL
GO TO DINNER TOGETHER.

13:38.218 --> 13:41.554
NO, I DON'T THINK
THAT'S GONNA WORK.

13:41.588 --> 13:43.891
- BOB, CAN I ASK YOU SOMETHING?
- OF COURSE.

13:43.924 --> 13:47.127
- WHAT IS GOING ON?
- YOU SKIPPED OUT ON
TALKING TO YOUR DAUGHTER...

13:47.160 --> 13:50.230
TO HANG OUT WITH JOEL
BUT YOU DON'T WANT TO SEE
HIS WIFE.

13:50.263 --> 13:53.867
I FIND OUT YOU BRIBED SOMEBODY
TO GET INTO THIS ROOM WHICH NOT
ONLY ISN'T A NONSMOKING ROOM,

13:53.901 --> 13:57.137
- BUT IT'S ALSO WHERE YOU
THINK WE SPENT OUR HONEYMOON.
- [ Phone Beeps ]

13:57.170 --> 14:01.474
YOU BROUGHT YOUR UNIT ISSUE
SATELLITE PHONE AND IT WANTS
TO TALK TO YOU ON OUR VACATION.

14:01.508 --> 14:04.878
- KIM--
- NO. I KNOW WHAT GUILTY
KNOWLEDGE LOOKS LIKE.

14:04.912 --> 14:08.815
- NOW WHAT IS GOING ON?
- [ Beeping Continues ]

14:08.848 --> 14:13.053
OH. ALL RIGHT.
SO IT HAS TO DO WITH WORK?

14:14.787 --> 14:17.024
DOES IT HAVE
TO DO WITH WORK?

14:18.591 --> 14:21.261
IT HAS TO DO WITH WORK.

14:27.867 --> 14:30.003
[ Turns Faucet On ]

14:30.037 --> 14:34.374
LOOK, SOMEONE HAS BEEN
DOWNLOADING TOP-SECRET DATA
FROM AIR FORCE LABS IN KIRTLAND.

14:34.407 --> 14:36.376
THEY'VE BEEN PASSING IT
ON TO THE CHINESE.

14:36.409 --> 14:39.179
THIS MATERIAL WOULD GIVE
THE CHINESE PARITY IN AEROSPACE.

14:39.212 --> 14:41.381
THEY THINK IT'S OUR FRIENDS
IN THE NEXT ROOM.

14:41.414 --> 14:47.020
MY JOB IS TO OBSERVE, GET CLOSE
TO THE MAN, SEE IF I CAN
CATCH HIM OUT MAKING A DROP.

14:47.054 --> 14:50.123
AND THIS IS
MY GETAWAY VACATION?

14:50.157 --> 14:53.160
YOU BROUGHT ME
ON A MISSION?

14:57.897 --> 15:00.767
MR. GREEN, REPORT.

15:00.800 --> 15:04.704
IT'S NOT FROM THE BARGAIN BIN.
MORE LIKE THE FINEST
SWISS WATCH FACTORY.

15:04.737 --> 15:07.774
- [ Jonas ]
CAN YOU GUYS DEFEAT IT?
- IF WE HAD ANOTHER WEEK.

15:07.807 --> 15:11.644
- IT'S GONNA BE HARDER
TO PUT IT BACK THAN REMOVE IT.
- CAN YOU DO IT?

15:11.678 --> 15:14.281
IT'S LIKE GOING UP
A DRY HILL BACKWARDS
ON CROSS-COUNTRY SKIS.

15:14.314 --> 15:17.550
GO ON THEN.
MR. WHITE, WHAT DO YOU SEE?

15:17.584 --> 15:19.586
IT'S DEFINITELY A LAUNCH TUBE.

15:19.619 --> 15:21.488
MILITARY?
LOOKS LIKE IT.

15:21.521 --> 15:24.291
WHAT'S THE SECURITY CAMERA
SITUATION IN THIS BUILDING?

15:24.324 --> 15:27.327
SYSTEM WAS DISABLED.
SO WE GOT NO PICTURES
OF WHO BROUGHT THIS HERE.

15:27.360 --> 15:29.929
WE KEPT THE SYSTEM OFF IN CASE
HE WIRED IT TO WATCH US.

15:29.963 --> 15:32.132
GOOD.
FLAG THE FOLLOWING.

15:32.165 --> 15:38.105
NAVY SEALs, RANGERS, ARMY
ORDNANCE DISPOSAL, DELTAS,
C.I.A. SPECIAL PROJECTS.

15:38.138 --> 15:41.808
LOOK FOR ANY AND
ALL BUILDING PERSONNEL
WITH MILITARY BACKGROUNDS.

15:41.841 --> 15:43.810
RIGHT NOW, PLEASE.
[ Snapping Fingers ]

15:48.615 --> 15:50.683
I STILL WANT TO LOOK
AT THAT TUBE.

15:50.717 --> 15:54.687
IT'S ABOUT EIGHT INCHES ACROSS.
NOT YOUR STANDARD PIPE BOMB.

16:01.461 --> 16:04.697
- IT'S A MORTAR TOP.
- TELL ME SOMETHING
I DON'T KNOW.

16:04.731 --> 16:06.666
I CAN SEE SOMETHING,
BUT THERE'S NOT ENOUGH LIGHT.

16:06.699 --> 16:08.468
LET ME.

16:08.501 --> 16:11.371
WAIT!

16:11.404 --> 16:14.074
JUST WHAT HE WANTS
US TO DO.

16:16.576 --> 16:18.811
YEAH.

16:18.845 --> 16:21.514
BOSS?
YES?

16:21.548 --> 16:24.517
- HE'S PUT IN A PHOTO CELL CHIP.
- WHAT'S THAT MEAN?

16:24.551 --> 16:27.054
IT MEANS WE CAN'T LOOK
AT WHAT'S INSIDE.

16:27.087 --> 16:30.190
- ANY ARTIFICIAL LIGHT
WITH SUFFICIENT FREQUENCY--
- HOW ABOUT A LOW FREQUENCY?

16:30.223 --> 16:32.492
- SETS IT OFF.
- HOW ABOUT A LOW FREQUENCY?

16:32.525 --> 16:35.228
CHEM LIGHT'S
THE SAFE WAY TO GO.
CHEM LIGHTS?

16:35.262 --> 16:39.099
- WILL THAT SLOW YOU DOWN?
- HASTE MAKES WASTE.

16:40.533 --> 16:42.835
DO IT THEN.

16:52.011 --> 16:56.216
- MR. WHITE, WHERE YOU AT?
- I JUST HAD A PRETTY THOUGHT.
BEEN WONDERING.

16:56.249 --> 17:01.388
EIGHT INCH S.P.,
STANDARD ROUND.

17:01.421 --> 17:03.423
THEY PUT IT IN THIS ROOM
SO THEY COULD HAVE A SKYLIGHT.

17:03.456 --> 17:05.992
IN ADDITION TO BLOWING OUT
THE EXECUTIVE SUITE,

17:06.025 --> 17:09.929
THEY'LL SEND AN ORDNANCE
UP THROUGH THE GLASS
INTO THE SKY OVER ATLANTA.

17:09.962 --> 17:12.532
- DISPERSE WHAT'S EVER
IN THAT CANISTER.
- DOUBLE-ARMING MECHANISM?

17:12.565 --> 17:15.034
YEAH. FIRST THE MORTAR FIRES,
THEN THE SHELL SPINS.

17:15.068 --> 17:18.271
PROBABLY SET FOR WHEN IT REACHES
ABOUT A THOUSAND R.P.M.'s.

17:20.973 --> 17:25.678
X-RAY CAN'T SEE WHAT'S
INSIDE THE SHELL BECAUSE
THE SHELL'S LINED WITH LEAD.

17:25.712 --> 17:29.416
HERE'S THE FUNNY PART.
YOU'RE NOT SUPPOSED TO PICK UP
ANY READING THROUGH THE LEAD.

17:29.449 --> 17:34.421
- KEEP GOING. SPEAK FAST.
- GEIGER POPPED HER LIPS
LIKE A TIJUANA STRIPPER.

17:34.454 --> 17:37.724
- SPILLED SOME PLUTONIUM
GETTING IT IN THE GAS TANK.
- THAT'S WHAT I'M THINKING.

17:37.757 --> 17:41.294
GETTING RIGHT BACK TO YOU.

17:41.328 --> 17:45.064
LISTEN UP, PEOPLE.
JUST RECEIVED CRITICAL
INFORMATION.

17:45.098 --> 17:48.268
WE ARE NOW IN A HOT ZONE.
I REPEAT, HOT.

17:48.301 --> 17:51.204
THIS ENTIRE BUILDING IS NOW
UNDER MY JURISDICTION.

17:51.238 --> 17:53.940
I WANT A TELEVISION SET
TO WATCH LOCAL NEWS CHANNELS.

17:53.973 --> 17:56.243
WE NEED TO STAY ON TOP
OF ANY LEAKS TO THE PRESS.

17:56.276 --> 18:00.247
AGENT BLUMAN, I NEED A FRESH
CUP OF COFFEE AND LOW-SECURE
FREQUENCIES TO MY MEN.

18:00.280 --> 18:02.915
- YOU ARE NOW UNDER MY COMMAND.
- BUT--

18:02.949 --> 18:05.785
THE I.E.D. IN QUESTION
HAS NUCLEAR CAPABILITY.

18:05.818 --> 18:07.987
YOU'RE IN MY HOUSE NOW.

18:10.990 --> 18:14.494
HOW LONG BEFORE
I CAN WATCH THE LOCAL NEWS?
[ Man ] 45 SECONDS.

18:14.527 --> 18:17.297
THE MONEY IS READY.
MONEY?

18:17.330 --> 18:20.167
THIS IS MY BUILDING.
I'M GONNA MAKE
THE PAYMENT AND END IT.

18:20.200 --> 18:23.403
- YOU DO UNDERSTAND THAT
THIS BOMB MAY BE NUCLEAR?
- YES, I DO UNDERSTAND.

18:23.436 --> 18:26.072
YOU READ THE NOTE.
IF I GO BY MYSELF AND
PAY THE FIVE MILLION,

18:26.105 --> 18:28.074
HE'LL TELL US HOW
TO DISARM IT.

18:28.107 --> 18:30.277
YOU CAN'T PAY NOW.
ONE REASON WHY NOT?

18:30.310 --> 18:34.347
YOU PAY NOW, WHAT HAPPENS NEXT
WEEK, NEXT MONTH WHEN A BIGGER,
BETTER ONE SHOWS UP?

18:34.381 --> 18:39.018
LOOK, I NEED YOUR HELP.
WE GOTTA GET THE OCCUPANTS
IN THIS BUILDING OUT OF HERE.

18:39.051 --> 18:40.520
- YOU CAN AID IN THE EVACUATION.
- BUT--

18:40.553 --> 18:43.156
BUT NOTHING.
YOU'RE UNDER MY AUTHORITY.

18:43.190 --> 18:47.260
AND THIS BUILDING BELONGS TO ME
AS LONG AS THAT BOMB IS GLOWING.
MR. GREEN.

18:47.294 --> 18:50.997
HOW'S THAT EVAC PLAN COMING?
IT IS MY LIFE'S WORK.

18:51.030 --> 18:54.367
THERE'S AN OLD VAULT
DOWN IN THE BASEMENT.
FOOTING'S ARE ADOBE WITH WOOD.

18:54.401 --> 18:57.003
REVAMPED 10 YEARS AGO
TO BE HURRICANE RESISTANT.

18:57.036 --> 19:00.039
YOU CHARGE IT ON THIS
WALL HERE, IT'LL MELT LIKE
GRAHAM CRACKERS AND MILK.

19:00.072 --> 19:03.009
IT'LL BE SMOOTH.
UPDATE.

19:03.042 --> 19:06.446
- THERE'S ONLY ONE WAY TO LEAVE
THIS BUILDING-- UNOBSERVED.
- AND WHY IS THAT?

19:06.479 --> 19:08.781
THE BOMBER COULD BE WATCHING.
HE'S SITTING OUT THERE.

19:08.815 --> 19:12.219
HE SEES THE THRONGS POURING OUT
OF HERE, COULD GET CRANKY
AND PUSH THE BUTTON.

19:12.252 --> 19:14.187
HE'S WATCHING US FROM WHERE?
POINT?

19:14.221 --> 19:18.325
ONLY WAY HE'D WATCH IS
FROM FAR AWAY. OTHERWISE,
IT'S A SUICIDE MISSION.

19:22.362 --> 19:24.964
HAVE YOUR PEOPLE ON THE OUTSIDE
SEARCH FOR REMOTE CAMERAS.

19:24.997 --> 19:27.900
TWO SQUARE BLOCK RADIUS
AROUND OUR LOCATION.

19:27.934 --> 19:31.371
HE'S WATCHING US FROM SOMEWHERE.
HOW WE GONNA FOOL HIM?
WE CAN MAKE AN EXIT.

19:31.404 --> 19:33.873
WE'LL BLOW A HOLE
IN THIS BASEMENT WALL.

19:33.906 --> 19:37.410
ACCESS US TO UNDERGROUND
ATLANTA. A WHOLE SECOND CITY
CARVED OUT RIGHT BENEATH US.

19:37.444 --> 19:40.079
- YOU GOTTA GUARANTEE ME ZERO
VIBRATION OR IT'S A NO GO.
- DONE.

19:40.112 --> 19:42.849
I WANT YOUR TEAM MOVING FLOOR
TO FLOOR PREPARING...

19:42.882 --> 19:45.918
FOR THE QUIETEST,
MOST INCONSPICUOUS
FIRE DRILL ON RECORD.

19:45.952 --> 19:48.221
- YOU GOT IT.
- WHAT'S IN THE BASEMENT?

19:48.255 --> 19:50.323
THE OLD VAULT.
ANY STUFF IN THERE
YOU'RE GONNA NEED?

19:50.357 --> 19:53.593
YOU'RE GONNA BLOW
A HOLE IN MY BUILDING?
WELL, THE ROOF IS COMING OFF.

19:53.626 --> 19:57.364
WE CAN GIVE YOU SHOES
TO MATCH THE HAT.

19:58.631 --> 20:01.601
[ Door Opens ]

20:01.634 --> 20:03.736
LOOK, YOU CAN'T LEAVE NOW.
NO?

20:03.770 --> 20:07.440
NO. IT'LL HARM THE OPERATION.
THAT'S WHAT CONCERNS YOU?

20:07.474 --> 20:10.743
WHAT ABOUT WHAT HARMS
YOUR MARRIAGE,
LIKE YOU LYING TO ME?

20:10.777 --> 20:13.179
IT'LL DRAW ATTENTION
IF YOU GO.
WELL, LET ME HELP YOU.

20:13.212 --> 20:16.783
YOU CAN TELL THEM
YOUR WIFE LEFT YOU. YOU CAN
SPEND YOUR VACATION WITH JOEL.

20:16.816 --> 20:19.118
JOEL IS COMMITTING TREASON.
HOW DO YOU KNOW?

20:19.151 --> 20:21.721
BECAUSE THE INTEL SAYS
HE HAD THE MEANS.
HE HAD THE OPPORTUNITY.

20:21.754 --> 20:23.790
HE HAS A CHINESE WIFE WHO
HE'S TRAVELED WITH OVER THERE...

20:23.823 --> 20:26.859
WHERE THEY PROBABLY
RECRUITED HIM AND HER.

20:26.893 --> 20:29.462
I DIDN'T MAKE THE CALL.
I'M JUST THE ONE WHO HAS
TO CATCH HIM.

20:29.496 --> 20:31.564
AND I'M LIKE WHAT?
THE BAIT?

20:31.598 --> 20:34.301
"OH, LOOK.
THERE'S A NICE COUPLE.
THEY GOT KIDS."

20:34.334 --> 20:36.769
NO, YOU WERE COVER.
A DISTRACTION GOOD ENOUGH
FOR ME TO DO MY JOB.

20:36.803 --> 20:39.906
I'M COVER?
YOU WERE NEVER MEANT
TO FIND OUT.

20:39.939 --> 20:43.810
THAT IS A LONG WAY FROM
"I'D CUT OFF MY ARM TO SPEND
ANOTHER NIGHT WITH YOU."

20:43.843 --> 20:46.779
LOOK AT IT LIKE THIS.
NO! I DON'T WANT
TO LOOK AT IT...

20:46.813 --> 20:48.615
BECAUSE YOU LIED TO ME.

20:53.953 --> 20:56.623
DID YOU TELL AMY
WE WERE HAVING DINNER?

21:00.159 --> 21:03.563
NO. SHE ASKED.
WHERE'S HIS MOM GONNA BE?

21:03.596 --> 21:06.999
WHAT'S HER NAME? EVELYN?
IS SHE GONNA BE BACK
IN THE ROOM?

21:07.033 --> 21:11.638
SHE TALKED
ABOUT TAKING THE TWINS
TO FIND PIZZA SOMEPLACE.

21:11.671 --> 21:14.841
IT'S A PERFECT CHANCE
FOR US TO GET IN THAT ROOM,
LOOK FOR THE DATA.

21:14.874 --> 21:18.110
CALL AMY.
TELL HER WE'LL BE THERE.

21:19.846 --> 21:21.714
IS THAT AN ORDER?

21:23.483 --> 21:27.119
IT IS FOR ME.
ARE YOU UP TO THIS?

21:29.822 --> 21:32.992
[ Kim ]
SO, LANGUAGE SCHOOL?
[ Amy ] YEAH.

21:33.025 --> 21:35.695
JOEL WAS FIRST IN MY CLASS
TO LEARN TO COUNT TO 10.

21:35.728 --> 21:39.098
[ Counting In
Foreign Language ]

21:39.131 --> 21:41.334
THAT'S GOOD, DARLING.
[ Laughing ]

21:41.368 --> 21:45.538
MOST AMERICANS, TAKES THEM
ALMOST A YEAR TO LEARN TO
DIFFERENTIATE BETWEEN THE TONES.

21:45.572 --> 21:49.642
EVERY TIME WE GO TO TAIPEI
TO VISIT MY FAMILY, HE GETS
COMPLIMENTS ON HIS ACCENT.

21:49.676 --> 21:52.812
OH, HONEY, IT'S ALMOST
SERENA'S BEDTIME.
WE SHOULD CALL IN.

21:52.845 --> 21:55.682
IT'S ALL RIGHT.
YOU KNOW WHAT?
I'LL DO IT THIS TIME.

21:55.715 --> 21:59.486
WON'T TAKE LONG.
YOU GUYS GO AHEAD
AND START, ALL RIGHT?

22:00.820 --> 22:03.956
SO, BOB ALSO HAS
A THING FOR LANGUAGES.

22:03.990 --> 22:05.825
REALLY?

22:49.101 --> 22:51.370
[ Babies Crying ]
[ Evelyn ]
DON'T CRY.

22:51.404 --> 22:54.373
WHAT'S THE MATTER?
YOU GONNA THROW UP?
[ Crying Continues ]

22:54.407 --> 22:58.945
NO. WE HAD SUCH A GOOD TIME.
WHAT'S THE MATTER?

22:58.978 --> 23:03.115
COME ON.
LET'S GET YOUR P.J.'s ON.

23:03.149 --> 23:05.117
[ Crying Continues ]

23:06.919 --> 23:10.557
GOOD BOYS. AHH.

23:10.590 --> 23:12.559
WELL, NEW MEXICO
IS BEAUTIFUL.

23:12.592 --> 23:16.095
ALBUQUERQUE, IT'S
A BEAUTIFUL LOCATION.

23:16.128 --> 23:18.364
- EXCEPT WE'RE BEING
TRANSFERRED.
- AMY.

23:18.397 --> 23:22.034
WHAT? WE CAN TALK ABOUT IT.
JOEL'S NOT GETTING
THE POSTINGS HE WOULD LIKE.

23:22.068 --> 23:24.871
- IT'S FINE.
- IT'S LIKE HE'S BUMPING UP
AGAINST SOMETHING.

23:24.904 --> 23:27.674
LET'S FACE IT.
WITH A WIFE FOREIGN-BORN--

23:29.976 --> 23:32.812
I'M SORRY.
IT'S A VACATION, RIGHT?

23:32.845 --> 23:35.482
BOB'S MISSING A GREAT MEAL.

23:35.515 --> 23:37.884
IT'S NOT YOU
THAT'S HOLDING ME BACK.

23:37.917 --> 23:41.120
THEN WHAT IS?
HEY, GUYS.
SORRY.

23:41.153 --> 23:43.456
[ Sighs ]
WELL, SERENA MISSES YOU.

23:43.490 --> 23:45.758
BUT SHE'S FINE.
SHE SENDS HER LOVE.

23:45.792 --> 23:48.260
SHE DOESN'T,
HOWEVER, MISS ME.

23:48.294 --> 23:50.897
BUT SHE WANTS ME
TO BRING HER BACK A DOLL.
WHICH GOES TO SHOW YOU--

23:50.930 --> 23:52.965
HOW IS IT?
NOT BAD.

23:52.999 --> 23:54.834
YEAH?

24:08.114 --> 24:10.282
[ Machine Beeps ]

24:11.784 --> 24:14.521
I WANT YOU TO BE
THE FIRST PERSON
OUT OF THE EVAC.

24:14.554 --> 24:19.726
IF WE ALL DIE TODAY, I WANT
YOU TO GET THIS TO SOMEONE
WHO CAN MAKE SENSE OF IT.

24:25.364 --> 24:27.266
I HAVE THE GOVERNOR
ON THE LINE.

24:27.299 --> 24:30.036
- AND?
- AND I NEED TO GIVE HIM A GOOD
REASON TO TELL THE MAYOR...

24:30.069 --> 24:33.339
TO EVACUATE THE CITY
WITHOUT HIM TELLING
THE PRESS WHAT'S GOING ON.

24:35.875 --> 24:39.679
PULL UP A WEATHER REPORT,
PLEASE.

24:41.147 --> 24:44.083
GIVE ME THE PHONE.
BEST IDEA YOU HAD TODAY.

24:47.019 --> 24:50.523
YES, SIR.
I NEED THE CITY
OF ATLANTA EVACUATED.

24:50.557 --> 24:55.061
IN THE INTEREST OF SECURITY.
LESS THAN FOUR HOURS, SIR.

24:55.094 --> 24:59.198
THERE'S A STORM COMING
IN TWO HOURS AND THERE'S
A MASSIVE CHLORINE LEAK.

24:59.231 --> 25:04.403
MY BOSS?
MY BOSS IS THE PRESIDENT
OF THE UNITED STATES, SIR.

25:04.436 --> 25:07.574
NO. YOU HAVE
THOSE NUMBERS, SIR.

25:07.607 --> 25:12.745
IF YOU REFER TO PLAN
STARLIGHT ALPHA ONE,
THAT WILL--

25:12.779 --> 25:15.715
I BELIEVE WE HAVE
TO TAKE THAT RISK, SIR.

25:15.748 --> 25:19.318
SIR, I HAVE BEEN PLACED HERE
TO TAKE THAT RESPONSIBILITY.

25:19.351 --> 25:24.223
AND IF I'M WRONG,
I'M CONFIDENT I WON'T BE AROUND
TO ANSWER FOR IT.

25:24.256 --> 25:26.593
YES, SIR.
CHLORINE LEAK.

25:26.626 --> 25:28.695
AN HOUR MAY NOT
BE ENOUGH TIME, SIR.

25:31.397 --> 25:35.835
- THANK YOU, SIR.
- YOU JUST LIED TO
THE GOVERNOR OF GEORGIA.

25:35.868 --> 25:38.871
IS THAT A SIN
OR JUST A CRIME?

25:41.774 --> 25:43.910
MR. WHITE?

25:43.943 --> 25:48.547
- THEY GOT SOME THEORIES.
- WE MAY HAVE FOUND
A WEAK LINK.

25:48.581 --> 25:52.384
- [ Jonas ]
YOU CAN DISARM IT?
- LIKE SPLITTING A WISHBONE.

25:52.418 --> 25:56.088
- MR. WHITE, THAT TRUE BY YOU?
- I DON'T LIKE
THE OVER-UNDER, BOSS.

25:56.122 --> 25:58.591
- LET'S GET THEM OUT OF HERE.
- WE'RE NOT GOING ANYWHERE.

25:58.625 --> 26:03.095
MR. WHITE,
WE NEED ALL HANDS.
YOU GOT 20 MINUTES.

26:03.129 --> 26:07.233
THAT'S ENOUGH TIME TO
ANSWER A QUESTION I HAVE.

26:07.266 --> 26:10.402
[ Jonas ]
ALL RIGHT.
GET THAT CAMERA IN CLOSER.

26:10.436 --> 26:12.605
LET'S GET A BETTER LOOK.

26:14.974 --> 26:17.744
CLOSER STILL.

26:24.283 --> 26:26.085
WHAT THE HELL?

26:30.790 --> 26:33.159
PULL IT TOGETHER, MAN.
I GOT A WIFE AND KIDS.

26:33.192 --> 26:35.695
DON'T WE ALL?

26:42.101 --> 26:45.071
YOU WILL COLLECT P.D.A.'s,
CELL PHONES, WALKIE-TALKIES.

26:45.104 --> 26:47.439
TELL THEM THE FIRE MARSHAL
WANTS CLEAR CHANNELS.

26:47.473 --> 26:50.743
FIND AND ASSIST ANYONE
WITH PHYSICAL LIMITATIONS.

26:50.777 --> 26:54.847
TELL THEM THEY WILL BE
IDENTIFIED, TAGGED AND DRIVEN
TO A DESTINATION FOR DEBRIEFING.

26:57.449 --> 27:01.988
MR. WALCOTT, AM I GONNA
HAVE TO HAVE SOMEONE PIN
YOUR EARS TO THE WALL?

27:02.021 --> 27:05.858
THIS IS MADNESS.
I'M PAYING HIM OFF.
NO, SIR. THAT IS THE WRONG CALL.

27:05.892 --> 27:10.629
MY BANK MANAGES $12 BILLION. WE
CAN PLAY THIS GAME LONGER THAN
ANY ONE OF US WILL BE ALIVE.

27:10.663 --> 27:13.532
I'VE GOT KIDS LOOKING
FORWARD TO THEIR NEXT
THANKSGIVING DINNER...

27:13.565 --> 27:15.501
WITH THEIR
MOTHER AND FATHER.

27:15.534 --> 27:19.672
IF PAYING HIM
MIGHT STOP THE EXPLOSION,
THAT'S WHAT I'M GONNA DO.

27:19.706 --> 27:21.708
MR. WALCOTT?
LET HIM GO.

27:21.741 --> 27:25.111
GO WITH HIM,
ASSUMING THE EXPLOSION DOESN'T
SET THE WHOLE PLACE OFF.

27:25.144 --> 27:28.948
NO. WE NEED EVERY ABLE BODY
TO ASSIST WITH THE EVACUATION.

27:28.981 --> 27:31.851
HAVE PETERSON AND HIS MEN
TAIL MR. WALCOTT'S CAR
FROM A DISTANCE.

27:36.322 --> 27:41.193
[ Exhales ]
MR. GREEN,
GET YOUR POP READY.

27:41.227 --> 27:45.297
THE SOONER YOU DO YOUR THING,
THE SOONER I'LL KNOW IF
MY WIFE'S GONNA BE A WIDOW...

27:45.331 --> 27:48.134
AND THE SOONER
SHE CAN START DATING.

27:48.167 --> 27:50.536
OKAY.

27:50.569 --> 27:53.773
MR. GREEN, SOFT AND EASY.

27:56.876 --> 27:58.811
TEN SECONDS.

27:58.845 --> 28:01.881
WELL, YOU WANNA COUNT
OR SHOULD I?

28:03.449 --> 28:06.052
FORGET IT.
I'M BLOWING IT NOW.

28:06.085 --> 28:07.920
[ Explosion ]

28:14.761 --> 28:16.729
MR. GREEN?

28:20.432 --> 28:22.401
THAT WAS IT.
WE'VE GOT A NEW BACKDOOR.

28:22.434 --> 28:25.404
ADMIRABLE. VERY GOOD.

28:25.437 --> 28:28.340
NOW HELP WITH THE EVACUATION.
NO REST FOR THE WEARY.

28:28.374 --> 28:31.043
- WHAT? THAT WAS IT?
- WE HAVE OUR HOLE.

28:31.077 --> 28:34.814
ALL RIGHT, EVERYONE, GO.
WE GOTTA GET A LOT
OF FOLKS OUTTA HERE.

28:36.482 --> 28:39.185
[ Jonas Over Radio ]
ALL ESCORTS,
PROCEED AS PLANNED.

28:39.218 --> 28:42.188
EVERYONE SHOULD BE SAFELY OUT
IN SEVEN TO EIGHT MINUTES.

28:42.221 --> 28:44.891
LET'S GO.

28:48.795 --> 28:51.764
[ Man Whispering ]
WATCH IT. WATCH YOUR STEP.

28:53.132 --> 28:55.367
MR. WHITE, STATUS REPORT.

28:55.401 --> 29:00.472
THESE GUYS ARE WORKING ON
SOMETHING EQUIVALENT TO PROVING
THERE'S AN EASTER BUNNY.

29:00.506 --> 29:03.275
ARE YOU A BELIEVER?
HERE'S THE DEAL.

29:03.309 --> 29:06.112
TREMBLING SWITCHES,
MERCURY GAUGES,

29:06.145 --> 29:09.315
HIDDEN LEVELERS ON ALL
FOUR CORNERS, BLIND SPOTS.

29:09.348 --> 29:14.954
TOP, THIS BOMB WAS NEVER BUILT
TO BE DEACTIVATED OR DISARMED.

29:16.288 --> 29:19.025
IT'S MEANT TO GO OFF.

29:21.828 --> 29:23.996
THEN WHY ARE WE STILL HERE?

29:27.533 --> 29:29.936
WHAT'D YOU FIND?

29:29.969 --> 29:33.339
TELL ME. IF I'M GONNA
BE A PART OF THIS--

29:33.372 --> 29:36.976
MEMORY STICK HIDDEN
INSIDE A SHAMPOO BOTTLE.
MAYBE 15 GIGABYTES.

29:37.009 --> 29:40.446
AND NOW?
NEED TO FIND OUT WHERE HE MAKES
THE DROP AND WHO PICKS IT UP.

29:40.479 --> 29:43.515
THAT'S HOW I CATCH HIM
AND HIS CONTACT.
HIS WIFE IN ON IT?

29:44.783 --> 29:47.353
- BOB.
- [ Footsteps Approaching ]

29:47.386 --> 29:49.588
GUYS, JOEL'S OFF
ON AN ERRAND.

29:49.621 --> 29:53.259
YOU WANT TO COME BACK
TO THE ROOM? I CAN SHOW YOU
THOSE SWEATER PATTERNS.

29:53.292 --> 29:55.361
THEY'RE DARLING
FOR A NEWBORN.

29:58.330 --> 30:02.268
OH, GOSH. I'M SORRY.
YOU GUYS WANNA BE ALONE.

30:02.301 --> 30:06.138
- NO, IT'S ALL RIGHT.
- FORGET IT.

30:06.172 --> 30:08.975
WE'LL FIND YOU TOMORROW.
EXCEPT WE LEAVE TOMORROW.

30:09.008 --> 30:12.011
- YOU'RE LEAVING?
- JOEL GOT A CALL FROM WORK
OR SOME SUCH.

30:12.044 --> 30:15.747
ANYWAY, STOP BY BEFORE THEN
IF YOU CAN.

30:17.716 --> 30:20.786
HE'S MAKING THE DROP.
IT'S HAPPENING NOW.

30:20.819 --> 30:23.956
I NEED YOU TO CATCH UP WITH AMY,
FIND OUT IF YOU CAN
WHERE HER HUSBAND WENT.

30:23.990 --> 30:26.358
HOW?
NO CHANCES. NO RISK.

30:26.392 --> 30:28.727
JUST BE YOUR USUAL
CHATTY SELF, OKAY?

30:28.760 --> 30:31.397
ALL RIGHT, OFF YOU GO.

30:36.702 --> 30:40.172
KIM, SERIOUSLY.
I DIDN'T MEAN TO TAKE YOU AWAY
FROM YOUR HUSBAND.

30:40.206 --> 30:44.243
OH, BOB WILL BE FINE.
HE'S JUST WATCHING
THE GAME ON TV.

30:44.276 --> 30:47.479
WHICH SHOWS YOU WHERE
THE ROMANCE GOES.
YOU RESENT IT?

30:47.513 --> 30:49.581
IS JOEL COMING BACK?
WHAT?

30:49.615 --> 30:53.252
SOON? 'CAUSE I MEAN,
YOU'RE LEAVING TOMORROW.

30:53.285 --> 30:57.089
YOU GUYS MIGHT WANT A LITTLE
ROMANCE ON YOUR LAST NIGHT.

30:57.123 --> 30:59.425
WE'RE HAVING A LITTLE FIGHT.
DID YOU GUESS?

30:59.458 --> 31:02.261
NO.
YEAH.

31:02.294 --> 31:05.664
HE HATES IT WHEN I TALK ABOUT
THE FACT HE'S UNHAPPY.

31:05.697 --> 31:08.767
BUT HE IS.
WE'VE BEEN THINKING
ABOUT MAKING A CHANGE.

31:08.800 --> 31:11.037
WHAT KIND OF CHANGE?

31:11.070 --> 31:13.605
GETTING OUT OF THE AIR FORCE.

31:13.639 --> 31:16.508
I DON'T KNOW IF IT'S
WHERE HE WANTS TO SPEND
HIS WHOLE CAREER.

31:16.542 --> 31:18.744
I REALLY DON'T.

31:18.777 --> 31:20.746
YOU DON'T NEED
TO HEAR THIS.

31:20.779 --> 31:22.881
IT'S ALL RIGHT.

31:22.915 --> 31:25.051
HOW ABOUT YOU GUYS?
IS IT ALL--

31:25.084 --> 31:28.154
OH, WE HAVE OUR UPS AND DOWNS
GOD KNOWS.

31:36.095 --> 31:38.364
HE ON FOOT?
WHO?

31:38.397 --> 31:41.767
JOEL. HE LEFT HIS CAR KEYS.
HE'S RUNNING ERRANDS WITHOUT--

31:41.800 --> 31:43.735
HE SAID HE WANTED
TO TAKE A WALK.

31:43.769 --> 31:47.306
- YOU SHOULD CALL HIM.
HE ON HIS CELL?
- HE WANTS TO BE ALONE.

31:47.339 --> 31:50.542
I'M SORRY.
I DON'T MEAN TO MEDDLE,
I SWEAR.

31:50.576 --> 31:54.413
IT'S JUST--
IT'S JUST IT'S
YOUR LAST NIGHT HERE.

31:54.446 --> 31:56.915
YOU SHOULDN'T
SPEND IT FIGHTING.

31:59.085 --> 32:02.021
CAN I USE YOUR BATHROOM?

32:10.862 --> 32:13.599
I'M WITH AMY. JOEL LEFT
HIS KEYS. HE'S ON FOOT.
[ Faucet Running ]

32:13.632 --> 32:16.135
- YOU'RE IN THEIR ROOM?
- THEIR BATHROOM.

32:16.168 --> 32:18.270
I NEVER TOLD YOU
TO GO INTO THEIR ROOM.

32:18.304 --> 32:20.839
HE'S GOT IT WITH HIM.
HE CAN'T GO FAR.

32:20.872 --> 32:23.309
- I DON'T WANT YOU TO--
- I'M HERE. SO LISTEN.

32:23.342 --> 32:26.812
I SAW A NEW BOX OF CUBAN CIGARS
JUST OPENED. ONE WAS MISSING.

32:26.845 --> 32:29.781
GO SAY GOOD-BYE AND GET OUT
OF THERE. GO BACK TO THE ROOM
AND LOCK THE DOOR.

32:29.815 --> 32:31.984
OKAY.

32:32.018 --> 32:33.986
OH, I'M SORRY.
THAT'S ALL RIGHT.

32:34.020 --> 32:36.088
CODY SPILLED SOME JUICE.

32:36.122 --> 32:38.290
[ Turns Faucet Off ]

32:50.169 --> 32:52.138
FOR THE LATEST UPDATE
ON THIS BREAKING STORY--

32:52.171 --> 32:55.341
THE BUILDING IS 80% VACANT.
IT'S TIME FOR YOU ALL TO LEAVE.

32:55.374 --> 32:58.510
YOU SHOULD TAKE
A LOOK AT THIS.

32:58.544 --> 33:01.947
NO KNOWN SUSPECTS AT THIS
TIME IN THE MURDER OF WALCOTT
BANK PRESIDENT VAN WALCOTT...

33:01.980 --> 33:07.053
WHO WAS FOUND SHOT AND
KILLED ON AN ABANDONED HORSE
RANCH JUST OUTSIDE OF ATLANTA.

33:07.086 --> 33:09.221
WALCOTT WAS A PILLAR
OF THE COMMUNITY--

33:09.255 --> 33:11.690
[ Jonas ]
LOOKS LIKE OUR BOMBER
GOT HIS MONEY.

33:11.723 --> 33:14.493
- WHAT HAPPENED TO OUR MEN
FOLLOWING HIM?
- THAT'S A QUESTION FOR LATER.

33:14.526 --> 33:17.463
RIGHT NOW I NEED YOU TO HELP
WITH THE FINAL SWEEP.

33:17.496 --> 33:20.899
THEY'VE BEEN GOING AT IT
FOR A WHILE, SO I JUST
TURNED DOWN THE VOLUME.

33:20.932 --> 33:23.169
ALL RIGHT, PACK IT IN.

33:23.202 --> 33:25.371
YOU DON'T NEED ME?
NO. GET GONE.

33:25.404 --> 33:27.273
YOU TOO.

33:30.876 --> 33:33.045
MR. WHITE, REPORT.

33:33.079 --> 33:36.482
OUR FRIENDS HERE WANT TO SET
THEIR PLAN IN MOTION.

33:36.515 --> 33:39.485
IF IT'S NOT THEM GETTING
OUT OF THERE IN 10 SECONDS,
IT FALLS ON DEAF EARS.

33:39.518 --> 33:41.853
ALL THE TRIGGER SWITCHES
ARE UP HERE.

33:41.887 --> 33:45.424
RELAYS, THEY GO TO THIS
MECHANISM IN THE LOWER BOX
WITH THE C-4.

33:45.457 --> 33:49.395
WE CAN OUTRUN THE
ELECTRICAL CHARGE BY DETONATING
ALL OF THE TRIGGERING SYSTEMS.

33:49.428 --> 33:52.431
WIRES WILL MELT
BEFORE THE CHARGE
REACHES THE VENT.

33:52.464 --> 33:55.033
MR. WHITE, CONFIRM.
YOU GOT A COPY
OF THE X-RAY?

33:58.470 --> 34:02.074
- GO.
- THIS TOP BOX,
IT HAS THREE BLIND SPOTS.

34:02.108 --> 34:05.511
- IT'S WORSE THAN
TOSSING A COIN.
- IT'S ONE-BY-THREE.

34:05.544 --> 34:08.847
- SO IT'S A ONE-IN-SIX CHANCE
WE'D GET IT RIGHT.
- WE CAN DO THIS.

34:08.880 --> 34:11.617
NO. CAN'T AUTHORIZE IT
WITH A NUCLEAR I.E.D.
PACK IT IN.

34:11.650 --> 34:13.852
LOOK, WE CAN--
OUT.

34:13.885 --> 34:16.388
JOIN YOUR TEAM AT THE EVAC.

34:17.623 --> 34:19.758
LEAVE IT.

34:26.465 --> 34:29.067
MR. WHITE, YOU ARE GETTING
ON MY LAST NERVE.

34:29.101 --> 34:31.803
NO, LOOK. I LOVE
THIS SON OF A GUN.

34:31.837 --> 34:33.572
HERE.

34:35.006 --> 34:36.942
I WANT YOU
TO SEE SOMETHING.

34:39.945 --> 34:42.248
LOOK WHAT HE'S DONE.

34:44.650 --> 34:48.587
IT'S NOT NUCLEAR.
HE ONLY MADE IT
TO LOOK THAT WAY.

34:48.620 --> 34:52.391
- WHY?
- TO SHOW OFF.

34:52.424 --> 34:54.660
TO MAKE SURE
HE GETS THE CASH.

34:54.693 --> 34:57.896
WANTED TO PROVE TO US
HE CAN DO IT AGAIN,
NEXT TIME FOR REAL.

34:57.929 --> 35:00.299
IT'S NOT HOT?
YOU'D BET YOUR LIFE ON IT?

35:03.702 --> 35:07.339
HERE. WHY DON'T YOU
PULL THIS UP ON
THE MOBILE CAM?

35:10.942 --> 35:13.345
PICK IT UP.

35:13.379 --> 35:16.648
FOUND PLUTONIUM READINGS NEAR
THE MORTAR AROUND THE LEAD.

35:16.682 --> 35:19.251
KEEP IT MOVING.
WE'RE ON BORROWED TIME.

35:19.285 --> 35:22.188
WHY WAS I PICKING UP
A READING THROUGH THE LEAD?

35:22.221 --> 35:24.623
- AND THEN I FOUND THESE.
- AND?

35:24.656 --> 35:28.827
IT'S PLUTONIUM POWDER.
HE SPREAD IT HEAVILY
AROUND THE MORTAR.

35:28.860 --> 35:32.931
BUT HE DIDN'T KNOW
IT WAS GONNA DROP THE RESIDUE
ON ITS WAY OUT.

35:32.964 --> 35:35.534
REGULAR LIGHTS
DIDN'T PICK IT UP.
CHEM LIGHTS DID.

35:35.567 --> 35:38.437
- IMAGINE THAT.
- AND YOU DIDN'T TELL ME SOONER
FOR WHICH REASON?

35:38.470 --> 35:40.972
I KNEW THE MOMENT WE KNEW
THAT IT WASN'T NUCLEAR,

35:41.006 --> 35:44.443
WE WERE GONNA LOSE
THE AUTHORITY TO TELL
OUR FRIENDS TO GET OUT.

35:44.476 --> 35:46.445
- THEY'RE CONVINCED
THEY CAN TAKE IT DOWN.
- AND?

35:46.478 --> 35:50.282
YEAH. NO.
IT'S ONLY A THEORY,
AND IT'S A LEAKY ONE AT THAT.

35:50.316 --> 35:52.851
NOT OUR PROBLEM ANYMORE.
END IT.

35:57.823 --> 36:01.493
[ Cell Phone Beeps On ]
[ Sighs ]

36:01.527 --> 36:05.130
AGENT BLUMAN,
THIS IS MR. BLUE.

36:05.163 --> 36:09.235
THIS IS YOUR BABY NOW.
YOU HAVE OUR RECOMMENDATION
TO LEAVE THE BOMB BE.

36:09.268 --> 36:12.338
THE REST OF US
ARE EVACUATING NOW.

36:12.371 --> 36:14.940
WE'RE THE LAST ONES.

36:24.783 --> 36:27.353
[ Elevator Bell Dings ]

36:28.887 --> 36:31.857
[ Man ]
HOLD IT!

36:31.890 --> 36:37.696
[ Clears Throat ]
LAST ONES OUT GET THEIR PICTURE
IN THE PAPER.

36:37.729 --> 36:40.966
- BAD IDEA, FELLAS.
- NEW ORDERS FROM THE OLD BOSS.

36:49.275 --> 36:51.410
NOTHING WE CAN DO.

36:57.115 --> 37:00.519
AGENTS IN THE FIELD CONFIRM
WALCOTT IS DEAD.
THE MONEY'S GONE.

37:00.552 --> 37:03.722
MAN MAY HAVE BEEN A FOOL,
BUT AT LEAST HE WAS TRYING
TO HELP HIS PEOPLE.

37:03.755 --> 37:07.693
WE TRACKED HIM TO THE FIRST
DROP POINT. IT WAS A PAY PHONE
SENDING HIM TO A SECOND SPOT.

37:07.726 --> 37:11.363
HE SHOOK OUR TAIL
ON THE WAY THERE.
WORKS EVERY TIME BUT ONCE.

37:11.397 --> 37:14.433
IF I'D HAD THE CHANCE,
I WOULD'VE SHOT HIM
AND TAKEN THE LOOT.

37:16.167 --> 37:19.104
MY ADVICE--
OBSERVATION ONLY.

37:19.137 --> 37:21.039
TAKE THIS BOMB OUT BY REMOTE.

37:21.072 --> 37:24.776
WELL, THEY'RE CONVINCED
THEY CAN DO IT, SO I'M GONNA
GIVE THEM A SHOT.

37:24.810 --> 37:28.113
[ Explosion ]

37:28.146 --> 37:31.450
[ Alarms Blaring ]

38:08.987 --> 38:11.022
THIS IS NEW MEXICO,
OUR BACKYARD.

38:11.056 --> 38:13.659
JOEL'S ALREADY PUT TOGETHER
THE SWING SET.

38:13.692 --> 38:15.594
THAT'S NICE.

38:15.627 --> 38:19.264
I DON'T KNOW WHY
I'M SHOWING YOU THIS.
WE'RE NOT GONNA SEE IT AGAIN.

38:19.297 --> 38:21.032
I'M NOT GONNA SEE YOU AGAIN.

38:21.066 --> 38:24.970
IN TIMES OF STRESS--

38:25.003 --> 38:28.607
IN TIMES OF STRESS,
SOMETIMES WE LOOK BACKWARDS.

38:28.640 --> 38:31.943
I SHOULD BE GOING.

38:31.977 --> 38:34.880
[ Whispering ]
THEY'RE BOTH ASLEEP, FINALLY.

38:34.913 --> 38:37.816
AMY, WOULD YOU DO ME A FAVOR?

38:37.849 --> 38:41.052
- I LOST MY ROOM KEY AGAIN.
- WE'RE LEAVING TOMORROW.

38:41.086 --> 38:44.623
YES, BUT JUST IF
I HAVE TO GO OUT
AT SOME POINT WITH THE BOYS.

38:44.656 --> 38:47.693
WOULD YOU MIND
GOING TO THE FRONT DESK
AND GETTING ME ANOTHER...

38:47.726 --> 38:49.695
SINCE THE ROOM'S IN
YOU AND JOEL'S NAME?

38:49.728 --> 38:52.197
SURE, BUT--

38:52.230 --> 38:54.600
STAY WITH ME
FOR A MOMENT, WILL YOU?

39:24.896 --> 39:29.501
- ISN'T THIS NICE?
JOEL GOT IT FOR HER.
- IT'S VERY NICE.

39:29.535 --> 39:33.872
- [ Cell Phone Ringing ]
- EXPENSIVE, THOUGH.
AMY LIKES EXPENSIVE THINGS.

39:33.905 --> 39:37.008
[ Ringing Continues ]
IS THAT AMY'S PHONE?

39:37.042 --> 39:39.177
NO, MINE.

39:39.210 --> 39:43.749
DO YOU NEED TO GET IT?
NO. YOU ASK A LOT
OF QUESTIONS, DON'T YOU?

39:43.782 --> 39:48.520
SORRY?
USUALLY AMY HAS A RELUCTANCE
TO TALK ABOUT PERSONAL MATTERS.

39:48.554 --> 39:51.022
BUT YOU CAN'T SEEM TO LEAVE
PERSONAL THINGS ALONE.

39:51.056 --> 39:53.224
I DIDN'T MEAN TO BE RUDE.

39:53.258 --> 39:56.962
AND HERE I KNOW
NEXT TO NOTHING ABOUT YOU.

39:56.995 --> 40:00.766
JUST AN ARMY WIFE.
YOUR HUSBAND'S
IN SOMETHING CLERICAL.

40:00.799 --> 40:03.234
YES.

40:03.268 --> 40:06.137
I'D LIKE YOU TO LEAVE NOW.
WAS THERE--

40:06.171 --> 40:07.939
BEFORE AMY GETS BACK.

40:07.973 --> 40:11.242
SHE'S KIND OF WORKED UP,
MISS BROWN,
AND SHE NEEDS HER REST.

40:11.276 --> 40:14.379
AND I'D APPRECIATE THE PRIVACY
ON OUR LAST NIGHT.

40:14.412 --> 40:16.515
OKAY THEN.

40:28.093 --> 40:32.564
OH, GOD. ANSWER.
BOB, SOMETHING'S WRONG.
EVELYN-- JOEL'S MOM.

40:32.598 --> 40:36.234
- WHAT HAPPENED?
- SHE JUST KICKED ME OUT
FOR ASKING TOO MANY QUESTIONS.

40:36.267 --> 40:39.404
- WHAT DID YOU--
- SHE SUSPECTS.
OH, GOD. DID I JUST--

40:39.437 --> 40:42.307
HOLD ON.

40:44.943 --> 40:47.646
LOOK, I'LL CALL YOU BACK.

41:05.831 --> 41:09.501
BOB?
DON'T ANSWER THAT.

41:09.535 --> 41:12.571
WHY NOT?
LOOK IN MY RIGHT HAND.

41:18.176 --> 41:20.979
I'M GONNA WAIT
WITH YOU BACK THERE.

41:21.012 --> 41:23.248
SEE WHO COMES TO VISIT
THAT BENCH.

41:35.393 --> 41:38.329
[ Man On TV Chattering
In Spanish ]

41:39.765 --> 41:43.101
[ Knocking ]

41:50.909 --> 41:53.344
KIM. OH, GOD, KIM.

41:53.378 --> 41:55.714
AMY?
JOEL CALLED FROM THE AIRPORT.

41:55.747 --> 41:57.883
HE'S BEING FLOWN BACK NOW.
WHAT HAPPENED?

41:57.916 --> 42:00.552
HE'S BEEN ARRESTED.
OH, MY GOSH.
WHAT HAPPENED?

42:00.586 --> 42:04.155
EVELYN'S GONE TO BE WITH JOEL,
FOR WHAT REASON SHE HAD TO.

42:04.189 --> 42:08.226
KIM, WHAT DO I DO?
THE CHARGES AGAINST HIM.
THE BOYS ARE ASLEEP.

42:08.259 --> 42:11.997
I CAN'T--
AMY-- AMY, IT'S OKAY.

42:12.030 --> 42:15.000
YOU'RE RIGHT.
THE BOYS ARE THE MOST
IMPORTANT THING RIGHT NOW.

42:15.033 --> 42:17.736
NOW YOU JUST
GET BACK THERE--
BUT CAN YOU--

42:17.769 --> 42:20.872
I'LL COME JUST-- JUST
AS SOON AS I CAN, OKAY?

42:20.906 --> 42:22.841
EVERYTHING'S GONNA BE FINE.

42:22.874 --> 42:25.276
KIM, IT'S LIKE--
IT'S LIKE EVERYTHING'S--

42:25.310 --> 42:28.680
AMY, I'M SORRY.
NOW CAN YOU TAKE CARE
OF YOUR BOYS?

42:28.714 --> 42:31.683
- YEAH.
- OKAY THEN. I'M SORRY.

42:31.717 --> 42:34.620
I'LL COME JUST
AS SOON AS I CAN.

42:42.460 --> 42:45.130
SHE DIDN'T KNOW.

42:45.163 --> 42:47.132
MAYBE.
MAYBE?

42:47.165 --> 42:49.635
LOOK, WE DON'T KNOW
ANYTHING FOR CERTAIN.

42:49.668 --> 42:54.239
EVELYN COULD'VE PUT HIM
UP TO IT. SHE COULD SEE
HIS CAREER WAS GOING NOWHERE.

42:54.272 --> 42:56.742
HE NEEDED THE MONEY.
MY JOB IS DONE.

42:56.775 --> 42:58.910
YOUR JOB?

42:58.944 --> 43:01.913
KIM.

43:03.148 --> 43:05.183
THE JOB IS OVER.

43:09.454 --> 43:11.657
THIS IS HOW IT FEELS?

43:14.626 --> 43:18.429
[ Man On TV Continues
In Spanish ]

43:22.167 --> 43:25.070
[ Woman On TV ]
THEY SAY THE EXPLOSION WAS
CAUSED BY A NATURAL GAS LEAK.

43:25.103 --> 43:29.074
TWO REPORTED FATALITIES.
YEAH. ONLY TWO,
BUT THEY'RE BOTH DEAD.

43:29.107 --> 43:31.810
THEY ALMOST CONVINCED ME
TO BLOW UP WITH THEM.
REST IN PEACE.

43:31.843 --> 43:35.113
REST IN PEACE.
HERE'S THE LESSON.

43:35.146 --> 43:37.115
STUDY UP, FRIENDS.

43:37.148 --> 43:40.986
BECAUSE ONE OF THEM,
ONE OF THESE DAYS,
IS GONNA BE HOT.

43:55.233 --> 43:57.803
[ Call And Response ]
* FIRED UP
FIRED UP *

44:04.676 --> 44:07.713
* TWENTY-SEVEN
FIRED UP *
